## ✅ One‑Line Interview Answer

> A stale closure occurs when a function captures outdated state values from an earlier render, causing logic to run with old data even though state has changed.

***

## ✅ 10‑Second Interview Explanation

> Because closures capture values at the time they’re created, async callbacks or effects may use old state unless we use functional updates or proper dependencies.

